    "Body": " Senior Embedded Software Engineer Allumia.com - Seattle, WA Quick Apply Job Details Full-time$120,000 - $150,000 a year Benefits Health Insurance 401(k) Matching Paid Time Off 401(k) Qualifications Firmware Project Management Computer Skills Analysis Skills SoC Full Job Description Senior Embedded Firmware/Software/Systems Engineer We are looking for a creative, experienced embedded firmware engineer to join our team and help us move our advanced metering technology out of the research lab and into widespread commercial deployment. Vizi's mission is to transform the built environment by making energy metering and building health sensing so affordable and simple that it becomes ubiquitous. Our smart sensors provide actionable insights that let building owners and occupants improve efficiency, save on energy bills, and reduce carbon emissions. Vizi is a small but growing seed-stage startup consisting of energy industry experts, startup veterans, engineers, scientists, and big thinkers. Job Description \u2013 Develop embedded firmware for low-power microcontroller/wireless system-on-chips Develop low-level Linux network interface drivers Optimize firmware for energy consumption, while meeting high-level functionality goals Optimize data flow from ADC output to cloud across multiple wireless protocols Interface with Electrical Engineers for co-design of hardware and firmware The successful candidate will architect firmware, meet milestones, and deliver a reliable embedded product in the first 12 months Required Qualifications \u2013 2-6 years of experience writing firmware for resource-constrained embedded systems Demonstrable experience writing embedded Linux drivers Demonstrable experience shipping production code for embedded products Ideal Qualifications \u2013 Proficiency in C/C++, bash, python Experience with Cortex-M architectures Experience developing for RF SoCs Experience with single-board computers, such as Raspberry Pi Experience working with UART/SPI/I2C Hardware debug experience using oscilloscope and/or protocol analyzer Proven project management and organization skills Strong interpersonal and analytical skills Passion for the energy efficiency industry We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer, making decisions on the basis of merit, competence and qualifications, without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, marital status, nationality, disability, or any other legally protected status. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $120,000.00 - $150,000.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) Matching Health Insurance Paid Time Off Schedule: Monday to Friday Work Location: One location This Job Is Ideal for Someone Who Is: Dependable -- more reliable than spontaneous Adaptable/flexible -- enjoys doing work that requires frequent shifts in direction Detail-oriented -- would rather focus on the details of work than the bigger picture Autonomous/Independent -- enjoys working with little direction This Company Describes Its Culture as: Detail-oriented -- quality and precision-focused Innovative -- innovative and risk-taking Outcome-oriented -- results-focused with strong performance culture Team-oriented -- cooperative and collaborative Company's website: www.allumia.com Benefit Conditions: Waiting period may apply Work Remotely: Yes "
